Tensions are high at Charlotte Maxeke Secondary School in Tembisa. The learners here managed to break down the gate. They want to support their fellow peers at Phomolong Secondary School where the deputy headmaster was gunned down on Friday. eNCA's Heidi Giokos has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - There are tensions at the Charlotte Maxeke Secondary School in Tembisa. The school is near Phomolong Secondary school where the deputy principal was shot dead last week. READ: Deputy principal shot and killed According to the Basic Education Department, the shooting took place as she was driving out of school. Three gunmen allegedly appeared and shot three times through her passenger window. The MEC for Education in Gauteng, Panyaza Lesufi, is this morning visiting the Phomolong Secondary School, and the family of the slain deputy principal. eNCA's Heidi Giokos has more details. Courtesy #DStv403